additional_house_rules:
- We put a lot of time, love and effort into making a welcoming, comfortable space. Please enjoy respectfully. Please leave the apartment in the same excellent condition as you found it and treat as if it were your own home.
- Please be mindful of neighbors and building. Please keep noise to a minimum after 10pm. Do not buzz the entire building if locked out.
- Do not go on to the fire escape and please leave that window locked when unattended.
- We love the character that the LES contains but prefer the grit to stay outside, kindly remove your shoes.
- Please take rubbish & recycling out to garbage room on 1st Floor Landing.
description:
Comfortable, clean & updated 1 bedroom in authentic LES tenement building on best block of the neighborhood! Perfect for a couple.
Surrounded by trendy restaurants, hip shops, cozy cafes, coffee shops, art galleries & bars. 
Everything is right there, plus nolita, soho, alphabet city & east village are about a 10/ 15 min walk.
2.5 blocks to F and JMZ trains & 5 blocks to B D Subway.
*Please note: This is a 3 floor walk up (no elevator) but once you are in the space and hood, it'll be worth it!

Nolita, soho, alphabet city & east village are about a 10/ 15 min walk.

The apt is 2.5 blocks to the F and JMZ trains & 5 blocks to the B and D Subway.

There is a Citibike station at Allen and Hester (about 2 blocks).

Via is a great app to download to get around manhattan and to/ from the airports. It is a car share so not door to door and not the best if you are in a rush. Then you are better off taking a Juno, Lyft, Uber or local car service (Delancey (PHONE NUMBER HIDDEN)).

photos.caption: Serene and airy, open floor plan with art and design elements. View of living room and bedroom.
Bright, sunny bedroom faces lively, scenic street.
Queen bed with upholstered headboard & frame.
Luxury cotton percale, high thread count sheets.

Stearns & Foster Mattress and hypoallergenic down alternative
pillows and duvet.
Cozy living room with comfy couch, pillows, throws and plush, wool carpet.

View upon entry. 
Apt. outfitted with Wifi and Apple TV.
View of kitchen, bathroom and entry way from bedroom.
Small galley kitchen with oven and microwave/ convection oven.
Other side of kitchen with dishwasher and fridge.
Toaster, coffee maker and kettle for tea. Soma water filter in fridge.
Bathroom: pressurized shower head and shower caddy.

Bathroom: toilet and 
closet containing toiletries & essentials.

review.comments: Tim and Lulu's place is an elegantly designed apartment that felt like a hotel suite with luxe linens and towels, eco-friendly soaps and shampoos.   Welcoming and thoughtful, they gave us a nice bottle of wine at check in.  The kitchen had a beautiful fruit bowl, and snacks.  Everything is in the kitchen if you were staying a bit longer and wanted to cook.  We had a short stay and chose trying as many restaurants as possible.  The neighborhood has lots of great places to choose from, we used recommendations from Tim's guide to the neighborhood.  The subway is convenient and close.  One of a kind galleries, bars, shops, and restaurants around.  Wish we could have stayed longer.  Tim and Lulu were super accommodating and helpful for our trip.
